reports.query:
**This is Datakeepers dashboard!** 
 
Problem1: Given a country X, provide a list of airports operating in country X.

Problem2: Given a number of stops X, provide a list of airlines having X stops.

Problem3: Given a code share X for airlines, provide a list of airlines operating with code share X.

Problem4: Given the option to display active airlines, provide a list of active airlines if selected.
Airline aggregation feature:

Problem5: Given the option to display the country or territory with the highest number of airports, provide the country or territory with the highest number of airports if selected.

Problem6:Given a number of cities X, provide the top X cities with the most incoming and outgoing airlines.
Trip recommendation feature:

Problem 7: Given two cities X and Y, provide a list of routes connecting cities X and Y.

Problem 8: Given two cities X and Y and a number of stops Z, provide a list of routes connecting
cities X and Y with fewer than Z stops.

Problem 9: Given a city X and number of stops Y, provide a list of cities that can be reached from X
within Y stops.

Problem 10: Given city X, provide the path distance from city x to reachable city y and list it in the order of the best paths

reports.title: Problem1
reports.query:
MATCH (p:Airport) 
WHERE p.Country = "Iceland"
RETURN p.AirportID, p.Name, p.City, p.Country

reports.title: Problem3
reports.query:
MATCH (o:Route)-[r:FLOWN_BY]->(l:Airline)
WHERE o.AirlineID = l.AirlineID AND o.Codeshare = "Y"
RETURN DISTINCT l.AirlineID, l.Name, o.Codeshare

reports.title: Problem4
reports.query:
MATCH (l:Airline)
WHERE l.Active = "N"
RETURN DISTINCT l.AirlineID, l.Name, l.Active

reports.title: Problem2
reports.query:
MATCH (o:Route)-[r:FLOWN_BY]->(l:Airline)
WHERE o.AirlineID = l.AirlineID AND
	o.Stops = 1
RETURN DISTINCT l.AirlineID, l.Name, o.Stops
ORDER BY l.AirlineID

reports.title: Problem5
reports.query:
MATCH (p:Airport)
RETURN p.Country, COUNT(*) as Count
ORDER BY Count DESC
LIMIT 10

reports.title: Problem6
reports.query:
MATCH ()-[incoming]->(n)-[outgoing]->() 
WITH n, incoming, outgoing
WHERE n.City IS NOT NULL
RETURN n.City, COUNT(DISTINCT incoming) AS Incoming, COUNT(DISTINCT outgoing) as Outgoing, COUNT(DISTINCT incoming) + COUNT(DISTINCT outgoing) as Total
ORDER BY Total desc
LIMIT 10

reports.title: Problem7
reports.query:
MATCH PATH=(p:Airport)-[:BEGIN_ROUTE]->(o:Route)-[:END_ROUTE]->(p1:Airport)
WHERE p.City = "Orlando" AND p1.City = "Houston"
RETURN PATH, p.City, p.Name, p1.City, p1.Name

reports.title: Problem8
reports.query:
MATCH PATH=(p:Airport)-[:BEGIN_ROUTE]->(o:Route)-[:END_ROUTE]->(p1:Airport)
WHERE p.City = "Seattle" AND p1.City = "New York" AND o.Stops < 1
RETURN PATH, p.City, p.Name, p1.City, p1.Name, o.Stops

reports.title: Problem9
reports.query:
MATCH PATH=(p:Airport)-[:BEGIN_ROUTE]->(o:Route)-[:END_ROUTE]->(p1:Airport)
WHERE p.City = "New York" AND o.Stops = 0
RETURN PATH, p.City, p.Name, p1.City, p1.Name, o.Stops

reports.title: Problem10
reports.query:
MATCH PATH=(p:Airport)-[:BEGIN_ROUTE]->(o:Route)-[:END_ROUTE]->(p1:Airport)
WITH *, point({ longitude: p.Longitude, latitude: p.Latitude }) AS source, point({ longitude: p1.Longitude, latitude: p1.Latitude }) AS destination
WHERE o.AirlineID IS NOT NULL AND p.City = "Seattle"
RETURN PATH, round(distance(source, destination))/1000 AS travelDistance, p.City, p.Name, p1.City, p1.Name, o.Stops, o.AirlineID
ORDER BY travelDistance ASC
